</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="682" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[113,1089,220,500]" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,241,412,436]" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is composed of the Latin adjective 
<emphasis box="[811,919,413,436]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">purpureus</emphasis>
(purple) and the noun 
<emphasis box="[173,240,445,468]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">venter</emphasis>
(belly) to stress the conspicuous purple colouration of the abdomen; adjective.
</paragraph>
